SUMMARY:Deadline: Indigenous Screen Office: ISO Immersive Fund for Indigeno
 us XR Creators
DESCRIPTION:$500\,000 CAD funding programme from the Indigenous Screen Offi
 ce supporting Native American\, Alaska Native and Native Hawaiian storytel
 lers developing XR projects. Individual creators and Indigenous-owned prod
 uction companies may apply for up to $40\,000 CAD in development funding o
 r $80\,000 CAD in production funding. Applications open 30 May 2026\; dead
 line 30 June 2026 at 17:00 PST.\n\nOrganisation: Indigenous Screen Office 
 (ISO)\nLocation: Canada-based fund supporting Native American\, Alaska Nat
 ive and Native Hawaiian XR creators\nAward: Up to $40\,000 CAD (developmen
 t) or $80\,000 CAD (production) per project\; $500\,000 CAD total fund\nDu
 ration: Per project\n\nMore: https://www.indigenousscreen.ca
URL:https://www.indigenousscreen.ca
LOCATION:Canada-based fund supporting Native American\, Alaska Native and N
 ative Hawaiian XR creators
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:aws-imagine-go-further-faster-canada-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260428T195559Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260605
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260606
SUMMARY:Deadline: AWS Imagine Grant Canada 2026: Go Further\, Faster Award
DESCRIPTION:Canadian track of the 2026 AWS Imagine Grant for nonprofits lev
 eraging advanced cloud services (AI/ML\, HPC\, IoT). Up to $75K USD cash +
  $25K USD AWS credits\, plus AWS marketing support and technical specialis
 t access. Two-round selection: Round One closes 5 June 2026\; Round One no
 tification and Round Two invitations on 3 July 2026. Eligibility: nonprofi
 ts in Canada with a CRA-registered charitable organisation number (a 9-dig
 it Business Number\, often followed by RR0001 or similar). NOTE: this is a
  charities-only programme and is not open to individual artists\, research
 ers\, or for-profit studios.\n\nOrganisation: Amazon Web Services (AWS Ima
 gine Grant Program)\nLocation: Canada (CRA-registered charitable organisat
 ions only)\nAward: Up to $75\,000 USD unrestricted cash + up to $25\,000 U
 SD in AWS Promotional Credits + AWS marketing support and access to AWS te
 chnical specialists\nDuration: Two-round process. Round One closes 5 June 
 2026\; notifications 3 July 2026 with Round Two invitations issued the sam
 e day.\n\nMore: https://aws.amazon.com/government-education/nonprofits/aws
 -imagine-grant-program/aws-imagine-grant-canada/
URL:https://aws.amazon.com/government-education/nonprofits/aws-imagine-gran
 t-program/aws-imagine-grant-canada/
LOCATION:Canada (CRA-registered charitable organisations only)
